 0051: 
 0052: cdef class RenderComponent(MemComponent):
 0053:     '''The component associated with various renderers including: Renderer 
 0054:     and RotateRenderer. Designed for 2d sprites, but potentially useful for 
 0055:     other types of models as well. If not using for sprites, ignore **width**,
 0056:     **height**, and **texture_key** properties as they are designed for
 0057:     convenience when working with textured quads. Prefer instead to modify the
 0058:     properties of the **vert_mesh** directly.
 0059: 
 0060:     **Attributes:**
 0061:         **entity_id** (unsigned int): The entity_id this component is currently
 0062:         associated with. Will be <unsigned int>-1 if the component is
 0063:         unattached.
 0064: 
 0065:         **width** (float): The width of the sprite.
 0066: 
 0067:         **height** (float): The height of the sprite.
 0068: 
 0069:         **batch_id** (unsigned int): The batch the entity is assigned to. Read
 0070:         Only. If the entity is not currently batched will be <unsigned int>-1.
 0071: 
 0072:         **attribute_count** (unsigned int): The number of attributes in the
 0073:         vertex format for the model.
 0074: 
 0075:         **texture_key** (str): The name of the texture for this component. If
 0076:         there is no texture None will be returned.
 0077: 
 0078:         **render** (bool): Whether or not this entity should actually be
 0079:         rendered.
 0080: 
 0081:         **vertex_count** (unsigned int): The number of vertices in the current
 0082:         model (the **vert_mesh**). You should not modify the number of vertices
 0083:         while an entity is batched.
 0084: 
 0085:         **index_count** (unsigned int): The number of indices in the current
 0086:         model (the **vert_mesh**). You should not modify the number of indices
 0087:         while an entity is batched.
 0088: 
 0089:         **vert_mesh** (VertMesh): The actual VertMesh object containing the
 0090:         model information for this component.
 0091:     '''

static struct __pyx_vtabstruct_11kivent_core_7systems_9renderers_Renderer *__pyx_vtabptr_11kivent_core_7systems_9renderers_Renderer;


 0241:     '''
 0242:     Processing Depends On: PositionSystem2D, Renderer
 0243: 
 0244:     The basic KivEnt renderer draws with the VertexFormat4F:
 0245: 
 0246:     .. code-block:: cython
 0247: 
 0248:         ctypedef struct VertexFormat4F:
 0249:             GLfloat[2] pos
 0250:             GLfloat[2] uvs
 0251: 
 0252:     Entities will be batched into groups of up to **maximum_vertices**, if
 0253:     they can share the source of texture. This GameSystem is only
 0254:     dependent on its own component and the PositionComponent2D.
 0255: 
 0256:     If you want a static renderer, set **frame_count** to 1 and **updateable**
 0257:     to false.
 0258: 
 0259:     **Attributes:**
 0260:         **shader_source** (StringProperty): Path to the .glsl to be used, do
 0261:         include '.glsl' in the name. You must ensure that your shader matches
 0262:         your vertex format or you will have problems.
 0263: 
 0264:         **maximum_vertices** (NumericProperty): The maximum number of vertices
 0265:         that will be placed in a batch.
 0266: 
 0267:         **attribute_count** (NumericProperty): The number of attributes each
 0268:         vertex will contain. Computed automatically inside
 0269:         calculate_vertex_format.
 0270: 
 0271:         **vertex_format** (dict): describes format of data sent to shaders,
 0272:         generated automatically based on do_rotate, do_scale, do_color
 0273: 
 0274:         **blend_factor_source** (NumericProperty): Sets the Blend Source. for
 0275:         a visual exploration of this concept visit :
 0276:         http://www.andersriggelsen.dk/glblendfunc.php
 0277:         Options Include:
 0278:         GL_SRC_ALPHA, GL_ONE, GL_ZERO, GL_SRC_COLOR, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_COLOR,
 0279:         GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA, GL_DST_ALPHA, GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA,
 0280:         GL_DST_COLOR, GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_COLOR
 0281: 
 0282:         **blend_factor_dest** (NumericProperty): Sets the Blend Dest.
 0283:         See blend_factor_sourc for more details.
 0284: 
 0285:         **reset_blend_factor_source** (NumericProperty): The blend source
 0286:         will be reset to this after drawing this canvas.
 0287:         See blend_factor_source for more details.
 0288: 
 0289:         **reset_blend_factor_dest** (NumericProperty): The blend dest
 0290:         will be reset to this after drawing this canvas.
 0291:         See blend_factor_source for more details.
 0292: 
 0293:         **smallest_vertex_count** (NumericProperty, should be int): Used to
 0294:         estimate the number of entities that can fit in each batch at max,
 0295:         batch ComponentPointerAggregator will then be **size_of_batches** //
 0296:         **smallest_vertex_count** * **vertex_format_size**.
 0297: 
 0298:         **max_batches** (NumericProperty, should be int): The maximum number
 0299:         of space to reserve for this renderer. Will be **max_batches** *
 0300:         **frame_count** * **size_of_batches**.
 0301: 
 0302:         **size_of_batches** (NumericProperty): Size in kibibytes of each batch.
 0303: 
 0304:         **vertex_format_size** (NumericProperty): The size in bytes of the
 0305:         vertex_format to be used. Will typically be the result of calling
 0306:         sizeof on the struct being used.
 0307: 
 0308:         **frame_count** (NumericProperty, should be int): The number of frames
 0309:         to multibuffer.
 0310: 
 0311:         **force_update** (BooleanProperty): Set force_update if you want to be
 0312:         sure an Entity is drawn immediately upon being added instead of waiting
 0313:         for the next update tick. Useful if you want to have a static renderer,
 0314:         or if you are adding and removing an Entity every frame.
 0315: 
 0316:         **static_rendering** (BooleanProperty): Set static_rendering to True,
 0317:         if you do not want to redraw every Entity every frame. Usually used
 0318:         in combination with force_update = True.
 0319: 
 0320:         **update_trigger** (function): Invoke update_trigger if you want to
 0321:         force the renderer to redraw a frame. force_update = True will call
 0322:         update_trigger automatically on batching and unbatching of an Entity.
 0323: 
 0324:     **Attributes: (Cython Access Only)**
 0325:         **attribute_count** (unsigned int): The number of attributes in the
 0326:         VertMesh format for this renderer. Defaults to 4 (x, y, u, v).
 0327: 
 0328:         **batch_manager** (BatchManager): The BatchManager that is responsible
 0329:         for actually submitting vertex data to the GPU.
 0330: 
 0331:     '''
